a. Sustainable Landscapes Brazil Project
	‚Ä¢	DOI: 10.3334/ORNLDAAC/1644
	‚Ä¢	Description: Provides LiDAR point cloud data collected over selected forest research sites across the Amazon rainforest in Brazil between 2008 and 2018. The data are provided in 1 km¬≤ tiles and have been georeferenced, noise-filtered, and corrected for misalignment of overlapping flight lines.
	‚Ä¢	Usage: Utilize the cms_brazil_lidar_tile_inventory.kmz file to inspect tile coverage in Google Earth and identify tiles aligning with your Rio Xingu corridor.

b. LiDAR and DTM Data from Forested Land Near Manaus
	‚Ä¢	DOI: 10.3334/ORNLDAAC/1515
	‚Ä¢	Description: Offers LiDAR point clouds and digital terrain models (DTM) from surveys over forested areas near Manaus, Amazonas, Brazil, collected in 2008.
	‚Ä¢	Usage: While not directly over Rio Xingu, this dataset can provide supplementary data for comparative analysis or model training.

